@subsection XML Queries

The different functions in dyadic тОХXML are intended to construct XML queries.
An XML query extracts information from, or modifies information in, an XML
document. XML queries may differ considerably in their details, but usually
follow these top-level steps:

@enumerate
@item Read an XML document into, say, APL (APLтЖР0 тОХXML B or APLтЖР1 тОХXML B)
@item Optionally, display the structure of the document (3, 4, or 5 тОХXML APL)
@item Select a subset of XML nodes (= GNU APL member names, 6 тОХXML APL)
@item retrieve or modify the data in the selected XML nodes
 (with something like MEMBERSтЖР(тКВAPL) FUN┬и6тОХXML APLтЖРтОХXML followed by MEMBERтКГ )
@item Optionally, convert the modified XML document back to XML (0 тОХXML APL)
@end enumerate

